



AUDIO

A <audio> tag define sounds, represented using the <source> elements or the src attribute.

ex.1
  <audio>
   <source src="URL_1" type="audio/mpeg">>
   <source src="URL_2" type="audio/mpeg">>
  </audio>

ex.2
  <audio src='URL_1'></audio>

other attributes: autoplay, controls, loop etc.

HTMLMediaElement.currentTime is a property, giving the current playback time inseconds.
audio.currentTime = "seconds"


KEYBOARD

<kbd> is a phrase tag, defining keyboard input.
<kbd> Keyboard Input</kbd>
other phrase tag: <em>, <strong>, <var>, <code> 

Here is the JS code of keys:
http://keycode.info/


HTML DOM addEventListener() Method 
This method attaches an event handler to the specified element. 

Syntax: element.addEventListener(event, function)
example from w3schools:
 element.addEventListener("click", function(){ alert("Hello World!"); });

If you want to add event to an array, use forEach()
ex.
const keys = document.querySelectorAll('.key');
keys.forEach(key => key.addEventListener('transitionend',removeTransition));


Add/Remove Class to HTML element using JS & jQuery

JS: 
element.classList.add('className');
element.classList.remove('className');

jQuery:
$('element').addClass('className');
$('element').removeClass('className_1').addClass('className_2');





